      <h2>2023</h2>
      <p>
        The 2023 program covers fundamental and applied aspects of transformer‑based language models,
        from the original “Attention is All You Need” paper to contemporary systems like ChatGPT.
        Lectures by Elena Voita focus on bias, interpretability, and alignment, while hands‑on
        seminars by Ilya Boytsov introduce fine‑tuning, parameter‑efficient methods, and classic NLP
        workflows.
      </p>

